and what we're teaching a generation.

00:41:35.880 --> 00:41:39.360
It's about what Jesus did on the cross of Calvary

00:41:39.360 --> 00:41:43.420
and how much he loves us and how he died for us

00:41:43.420 --> 00:41:46.880
and he rose again and we get to serve him

00:41:46.880 --> 00:41:49.860
and please him with our lives.

00:41:49.860 --> 00:41:51.480
What a blessing.

00:41:51.480 --> 00:41:52.720
What a blessing.

00:41:52.720 --> 00:41:55.520
This Memorial Day, yes, we got some wonderful memorials.

00:41:55.520 --> 00:42:00.520
You might plan to go down to D.C. tomorrow

00:42:01.480 --> 00:42:02.640
to see some of those memorials.

00:42:02.640 --> 00:42:04.800
The Lord bless you if you do that

00:42:04.800 --> 00:42:06.040
because there'll probably be a lot of other people

00:42:06.040 --> 00:42:07.040
down there, amen?

00:42:09.760 --> 00:42:13.240
You'll be reminded of some important things

00:42:13.240 --> 00:42:15.880
but I want you to never get over the fact

00:42:15.880 --> 00:42:19.080
that every time you come into this church building,

00:42:19.080 --> 00:42:24.080
you're reminded of what Christ did for us

00:42:24.240 --> 00:42:27.760
and what our responsibility is to make him known

00:42:27.760 --> 00:42:28.980
to a lost and dying world.

00:42:28.980 --> 00:42:29.820
Let's pray together.

00:42:29.820 --> 00:42:31.200
Father, we love you.

00:42:31.200 --> 00:42:32.720
We thank you so much for loving us.

00:42:32.720 --> 00:42:35.920
We thank you for the portion of scripture.

00:42:35.920 --> 00:42:38.600
We thank you for the application.

00:42:38.600 --> 00:42:40.880
I pray, God, that you'd help us to train up

00:42:40.880 --> 00:42:43.720
a generation that's following us.

00:42:43.720 --> 00:42:46.220
God, even as we started there in the book of Jude,

00:42:49.120 --> 00:42:50.440
the faith has been delivered.

00:42:50.440 --> 00:42:53.000
We have the body of teaching of truth.

00:42:54.940 --> 00:42:57.500
We need to earnestly contend for the faith.

00:42:58.560 --> 00:43:01.180
We need to instruct a future generation.

00:43:02.800 --> 00:43:04.680
Oh God, I pray that it'd never be said

00:43:04.680 --> 00:43:08.280
that someone that grew up in this church

00:43:10.080 --> 00:43:13.320
would have no knowledge of what the statement

00:43:13.320 --> 00:43:16.520
on our Lord's supper table means, the significance of it.

00:43:16.520 --> 00:43:20.720
Oh God, help us to be faithful,

00:43:21.840 --> 00:43:23.800
to instruct a future generation,

00:43:23.800 --> 00:43:25.680
to influence a future generation

00:43:25.680 --> 00:43:28.560
that they would set their hope in thee,

00:43:28.560 --> 00:43:30.680
they would serve thee all the days of their lives.

00:43:30.680 --> 00:43:33.600
Bless, Lord, as we have an opportunity to come

00:43:33.600 --> 00:43:37.000
and just thank you, rejoice, commit our lives to you

00:43:37.000 --> 00:43:38.240
during the time of invitation.

00:43:38.240 --> 00:43:40.640
I pray that you'd have your will and way.

00:43:40.640 --> 00:43:42.240
We'll give you the glory for it's in Christ's name.

00:43:42.240 --> 00:43:43.840
We pray, would you stand with us?

